1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,490
Now he owns five, and he has purchased seventeen acres for his country estate.

2
00:00:05,760 --> 00:00:09,490
He's thinking and progressing right along toward his goal.

3
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:14,130
The three departments of your life are closely interrelated.

4
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:23,010
Each depends on the others to some extent, but the one department that has the most influence over the other departments is your work.

5
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:33,890
Thousands of years ago, the caveman who had the happiest home life and was most respected by his cavemates was the fellow who was most successful as a hunter.

6
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:37,970
As a generalization, the same point holds true today.

7
00:00:38,240 --> 00:00:44,370
The standard of living we provide our families, and the social and community respect we attain,

8
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:48,130
depends largely on our success in the work department.

9
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:58,929
Not long ago, the McKinsey Foundation for Management Research conducted a large-scale study to determine what it takes to become an executive.

10
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:03,809
Leaders in business, government, science, and religion were questioned.

11
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:09,730
Over and over again, in different ways, these researchers kept getting one answer.

12
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:16,370
The most important qualification for an executive is the sheer desire to get ahead.

13
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,890
Remember this advice of John Wanamaker.

14
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:26,370
A man is not doing much until the cause he works for possesses all there is of him.

15
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:30,209
Desire, when harnessed, is power.

16
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:36,929
Failure to follow desire, to do what you want to do most, paves the way to mediocrity.

17
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:43,089
I recall a conversation with a very promising young writer on a college newspaper.

18
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,689
This fellow had ability.

19
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:48,929
If anyone showed promise for a career in journalism, it was he.

20
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:54,449
Shortly before his graduation, I asked him, Well, Dan, what are you going to do,

21
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,610
get into some form of journalism?

22
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:59,490
Dan looked at me and said, heck no.

23
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:05,089
I like writing and reporting very much, and I've had a lot of fun working on the college paper.

24
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:09,329
But journalists are a dime a dozen, and I don't want to starve.

25
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:13,490
I didn't see or hear from Dan for five years.

26
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:16,929
Then one evening I chanced to meet him in New Orleans.

27
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:21,970
Dan was working as an assistant personnel director for an electronics company.

28
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:27,010
And he was quick to let me know that he was quite dissatisfied with his work.

29
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:33,569
Oh, I'm reasonably well paid, I'm with a wonderful company, and I've got reasonable security.

30
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:36,049
But you know, my heart isn't in it.

31
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:40,770
I wish now I'd gone with a publisher or a newspaper when I finished school.

32
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:45,329
Dan's attitude reflected boredom, uninterest.

33
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:47,650
He was cynical about many things.

34
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:54,209
He will never achieve maximum success until he quits his present job and gets into journalism.

35
00:02:54,560 --> 00:03:02,610
Success requires heart and soul effort, and you can put your heart and soul only into something you really desire.

36
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:10,130
Had Dan followed his desire, he could have risen to the very top in some phase of communication,

37
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:19,809
and over the long pull he would have made much more money and achieved far more personal satisfaction than he will find in his present kind of work.

38
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:29,970
Switching from what you don't like to do to what you do like to do is like putting a 500 horsepower motor in a ten-year-old car.

39
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:32,610
All of us have desires.

40
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,730
All of us dream of what we really want to do.

41
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,090
But few of us actually surrender to desire.

42
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:42,530
Instead of surrendering to desire, we murder it.

43
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:46,130
Five weapons are used to commit success suicide.

44
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:47,250
Destroy them.

45
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,530
They're dangerous.

46
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:51,650
1.
